Blackjack Rules

*Goal of the game is to add up your cards without going over 21
*If the cards in your hand add up to more than 21 - its called a 'Bust'
*Cards 2 to 10 - Counts as their facevalue
*Cards Jack, Queen & King - Count as 10
*Ace can count as 1 or 11 - You choose its value, depending on if your under 21
or over 21

If dealers first 2 cards are <17 they must choose another card

Game starts
need a deck of cards in a variable
need a math random to randomly choose a value from the deck

You get two cards and the values are added together
-If your two cards == 21, you win. Unless the dealer also draws 21, in that
case, you draw.
Dealer gets two cards (one number is hidden)

You get two choices:
Hit: Pick another card (number)
Stand: Stay at current value

User:
You must try to add your value up to as close to 21 as you can
If you go over 21 you lose

CPU (dealer):
If dealers first two cards are <17 they must choose another card if they are
17 or over they will stand



